1.  Open Context Menu and select "Create New"
2.  Select "Empty Object"
3.  Click "Position"
4.  Rename to "Clock"
5.  Create a child object
6.  Rename child to "Meshes (Scale Me)"
Note: in Desktop mode, use CTRL+T to open the Context Menu
7.  Open Context Menu and select "Create New"
8.  Select "3D Model"
9.  Select "Sphere"
Note: in Desktop mode, target an object with your laser, then press CTRL+R to secondary click
10. Secondary click on the Sphere
11. Open the Context menu and select "Open Inspector"
12. Change the name to "Hub"
13. Change the radius to "0.05"
14. Scroll to the "Grabbable" component and uncheck "Enabled"
15. Click "Position" and "Rotation"
16. Reselect the "Meshes (Scale Me)" slot and create a child
17. Change name to "Ring"
18. Click "Add Component"
19. "Assets"
20: "Procedural Meshes"
21: "Legacy UI"
22: "BevelRingMesh"
23: Change the "Width" value to "0.05"
24: Click "Setup Renderer"
25: Change the value for "Segments" to "60"
26: Change the x-axis rotation to "90"
27: Click "Add Component"
28: "Physics"
29: "Colliders"
30: "Mesh Collider"
31: Click on the Material Tool on your tool shelf to swap tools
32: Select a material for the hub (anything you like!)
33: Click on the hub mesh
34: Ooops!  If you accidentally apply the material to something else, open up your context menu and select "Undo".
35: Swap out materials and apply your chosen material to the ring
